''[[Inside Mac Games]]'' praised ''Glider PRO'' for its entertaining and non-violent gameplay, in addition to having a two-player mode that did not require modems or a network.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Myrick |first=Chris |date=December 1994 |title=Review: Glider Pro |journal=Inside Mac Games (Free Preview Edition) |volume=2 |issue=12}}</ref>

''[[AllGame]]'' editor Lisa Karen Savignano described ''Glider 4.0'' as "an interesting and fun game that will challenge people of all ages".

==Legacy==
Two monthly [[ezines]], ''GliderTech'' and ''The Cockpit'' were published between 1995 and 1997 following the release of ''Glider PRO''.{{citation needed|date=January 2017}} ''GliderTech'' published editorials, house reviews, house building tips and each issue was accompanied by a house or two with some examples of obstacles or techniques that could be used in house creation.

On 20 June 2014, a version of Glider for OS X 10.7 or later, was released on the [[Mac App Store]]. This version is also available for the iPhone and iPad as ''Glider Classic''.<ref name="touch-arcade">{{cite web |url=http://toucharcade.com/2011/09/26/john-calhouns-mac-classic-glider-coming-to-ios/ |publisher=Touch Arcade |date=2011-09-26 |author=Patterson, Blake |title=John Calhoun's Mac Classic 'Glider' Coming to iOS |access-date=2014-10-10 |archive-date=2014-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141004180626/http://toucharcade.com/2011/09/26/john-calhouns-mac-classic-glider-coming-to-ios/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Both are from Soft Dorothy LLC.

On 27 Jan 2016, the [[source code]], graphics, and sound data for ''Glider PRO'' were released on [[GitHub]] with the source code being licensed under the [[GNU General Public License]] v2. In addition, the source code for ''Glider 4.0'' was released under the [[MIT License]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Get a window into classic Mac dev with Glider source code |author=Nutt, Christian |website=[[Gamasutra]] |date=2012-02-16 |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/265823/Get_a_window_into_classic_Mac_dev_with_Glider_source_code.php |access-date=2016-08-02 |archive-date=2016-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721131024/http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/265823/Get_a_window_into_classic_Mac_dev_with_Glider_source_code.php |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sources for the Macintosh game, Glider PRO, written by John Calhoun and published by Casady & Green Inc. |url=https://github.com/softdorothy/glider_pro |website=[[GitHub]] |date=2016-01-29 |author=Calhoun, John |access-date=2016-01-30 |archive-date=2016-03-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321132956/https://github.com/softdorothy/glider_pro |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Added legal section to read me. · softdorothy/glider_pro@49a35bb · GitHub |url=https://github.com/softdorothy/glider_pro/commit/49a35bb15b7c6cf5febebc5c26bb65140a7c4957 |date=2016-01-31 |author=Calhoun, John |website=GitHub |access-date=2016-03-16 |archive-date=2016-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721130823/https://github.com/softdorothy/glider_pro/commit/49a35bb15b7c6cf5febebc5c26bb65140a7c4957 |url-status=live }}</ref>

